% You are an expert Python engineer. Write `pdd/commands/story.py`.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Role & Scope
  Implement the `pdd story` CLI command group as a `@click.group(name="story")` named `story_cli`,
  following the structural pattern of `pdd/commands/contracts.py`. The three subcommands (`add`,
  `list`, `link`) are thin wrappers over already-existing library functions in `pdd.user_story_tests`.
  No new library logic is introduced here.

% Requirements

<contract_rules>
R1 - Issue source resolution
For every `story add` invocation, the command MUST accept a positional argument that is a GitHub
issue URL, `#N` / bare integer issue number, or local `.md` file path. Inline text MUST require the
`--text` option to avoid ambiguity with URL/path detection. The command MUST fail with a clear error
message if the source cannot be resolved via `resolve_issue_source()`.

R1b - Story title override
When `--title <value>` is supplied, the command MUST use the supplied value (slugified)
as the story slug instead of the auto-derived slug. When `--title` is omitted and
`--text` is used, the command MUST derive a slug from the first few meaningful words
of the supplied text. When neither `--title` nor `--text` is used (URL/number/file
source), the slug is derived from the issue title or prompt file name as usual.

R2 - Dev-unit resolution
For every `--devunit <name>`, the command MUST resolve the name to prompt file(s) via a
`prompts/{name}_*.prompt` glob (excluding `*_LLM.prompt`), using the same logic as `pdd checkup`.
The command MUST fail early with a descriptive error if no matching prompt files are found.

R3 - Multi-devunit metadata preservation
When multiple `--devunit` or `--prompt` values are supplied, ALL resolved prompt paths MUST be
preserved in the `<!-- pdd-story-prompts: ... -->` metadata comment. The command MUST NOT keep
only the first value while silently dropping the others.

R4 - Dry-run no-write guarantee
When `--dry-run` is supplied, the command MUST NOT write any files. It MUST print the proposed
story file path and the list of linked prompts to stdout and exit 0.

R5 - Slug collision handling
When a story file with the same slug already exists and `--update` is NOT supplied, `story add`
MUST exit with a non-zero code and a clear error message pointing to `--update`.
When `--update` IS supplied, the command MUST merge the new prompt link(s) into the existing
story file's metadata comment without regenerating or overwriting the story body.

R6 - Path traversal prevention
Story output paths MUST be validated to ensure they resolve inside `user_stories/`.
Any path that resolves outside `user_stories/` MUST be rejected with a clear error.

R7 - Changed-files resolution
When `--from-changed-files` is supplied, the command MUST enumerate the set of currently
modified `.prompt` files in the repository and use them as the resolved prompt list.
It MUST fail with a descriptive error if the working directory is not a git repository
or if no changed `.prompt` files are found.

R8 - Regression generation handoff
When `--generate-regression` is supplied, the command MUST print a human-readable message
referencing issue #1700 and the follow-up `pdd test --from-story <story-file> --output ...`
command. The story command MUST NOT run pytest generation inline; deterministic test generation
belongs to `pdd test --from-story`.

R9 - Story list rendering
`story list` MUST render a formatted table with columns: story-id, file path, and linked prompts.
When `--with-regression-status` is supplied, an additional regression status column MUST be
included; that column MUST always show `-` until the #1699 traceability API is available.
Without `--with-regression-status`, no regression column is shown. When `user_stories/` is empty
or contains no story files, a friendly "No stories found" message MUST be printed and the command
exits 0.

R10 - Story link subcommand
`story link <story-file> --prompt <path>` MUST add the specified prompt link to the story file's
metadata comment (`<!-- pdd-story-prompts: ... -->`) and MUST NOT regenerate the story body or
modify any other part of the file. It MUST validate that the story file resolves inside
`user_stories/` (same R6 check) and fail with a clear error if it does not.
</contract_rules>

